    "summary": "Atlassian Takeover 2026",
    "description": "Atlassian are continuing their association with SydJS for another superb year, and you get the rewards.\n\nEach month Atlassian provides the venue, drinks, and pizza we enjoy at our meetings.\n\nAnd one month a year they go above and beyond and also provide us with an insight to the teams, the code, and the company.\n\nTo keep the tradition going we\u2019re clearing the runway and making room in March to hear from their team. And their team will be fresh from Atlassian\u2019s own EngFest, their twice yearly local, internal conference.\n\nWe\u2019ve got our sights on an international speaker and they\u2019ll be backed up by two of Sydney\u2019s own:\n\nShrey Somaiya will show us how static analysis can reduce your workload from weeks to seconds.\n\nCoby Plain will reveal \u201cGood Developer Habits\u201d that are bad at Atlassian scale.\n\nAnd stay tuned for news on our guest speaker\n\nIt\u2019s set to be a GREAT night!",
